# Trivy false-positive suppressions for OTForge container images.
#
# Firefox CVEs — fixed in Firefox 97 (February 2022).
# The workstation image installs Firefox from Mozilla's official apt repository
# (packages.mozilla.org) which provides version 151+. However, Mozilla's package
# version string (151.0.2~build1) lacks a Debian epoch prefix while Ubuntu's snap
# stub uses epoch 1 (1:1snap1-0ubuntu1). Because Debian epoch comparison treats
# any "1:x" as newer than any "x" without an epoch, Trivy incorrectly concludes
# the fix is not applied — even though Firefox 151 >> Firefox 97 (the fix version).
# All four CVEs were resolved in Firefox 97.0.2 (March 2022).
CVE-2022-25235
CVE-2022-25236
CVE-2022-26485
CVE-2022-26486
